# ─── DATABASE (PostgreSQL on Neon) ──────────────────────────────
# Create a FREE database at https://neon.tech (takes 1 minute)
# Neon gives you TWO connection strings in the dashboard:
#   1. Pooled connection  → DATABASE_URL  (used by the app at runtime)
#   2. Direct connection  → DIRECT_URL    (used by Prisma CLI for migrations)
#
# IMPORTANT for Vercel/serverless:
#   - DATABASE_URL MUST include pgbouncer=true (enables connection pooling)
#   - DIRECT_URL must NOT include pgbouncer (used for migrations only)
#   - Remove channel_binding=require if you get connection errors
#
# Paste them below, then run:
#   bun run db:push    # Create tables
#   bun run db:seed    # Populate real data (293 items, 7 users, sample challans)

DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@ep-XXXX-pooler.REGION.aws.neon.tech/DBNAME?sslmode=require&pgbouncer=true&connect_timeout=15"
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@ep-XXXX.REGION.aws.neon.tech/DBNAME?sslmode=require&connect_timeout=15"

# ─── FOR VERCEL DEPLOYMENT ───────────────────────────────────────
# In Vercel → Project Settings → Environment Variables, add BOTH:
#   DATABASE_URL  = the pooled Neon connection string (WITH pgbouncer=true)
#   DIRECT_URL    = the direct Neon connection string (WITHOUT pgbouncer)
# Then redeploy.

# ─── PDF CHALLAN AUTO-EXTRACTION ─────────────────────────────────
# The Sales "Upload Challan" feature auto-extracts fields from an uploaded
# Laxree challan PDF.
#
# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║  NO CONFIGURATION NEEDED — WORKS OUT OF THE BOX ON VERCEL     ║
# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
#
# DEFAULT METHOD: Text + Regex extraction (pdfjs-dist)
#   - Uses pdfjs-dist to extract raw text from the PDF
#   - Regex tuned to the Laxree challan layout extracts all fields:
#     challan number, date, quotation, client name/city/mobile, billing/
#     shipping address, GST, amounts, items (model, colour, qty, price, total)
#   - ZERO API key needed, ZERO external service calls
#   - Works on every cloud (Vercel, Netlify, AWS, anywhere)
#   - ~1-2 seconds per extraction
#   - Works on ALL text-based PDFs (the Laxree challan is text-based)
#
# OPTIONAL FALLBACK: VLM (for scanned/image PDFs only)
#   If text extraction fails (e.g. the PDF is a scanned image with no text
#   layer), the code falls back to a Vision Language Model. This requires
#   one of:
#
#   1. ZAI (sandbox only) — auto-provisioned in /etc/.z-ai-config, points at
#      internal-api.z.ai which is only reachable inside the Z.ai sandbox.
#      Nothing to do locally; will NOT work on Vercel (internal hostname).
#
#   2. Google Gemini (optional, for scanned PDFs on Vercel) — supports PDF
#      understanding natively. Get a free API key at:
#      https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
#      Then set in Vercel → Project Settings → Environment Variables:
#         GEMINI_API_KEY = <your free Gemini API key>
#         GEMINI_MODEL    = (optional) override default model
#
# IF YOU SEE "quota limit = 0" (only for the VLM fallback, rare):
#   Your Google Cloud project does not have billing enabled. Fix by EITHER:
#     a) Enable billing at https://console.cloud.google.com/billing
#     b) Create a NEW API key from a fresh Google Cloud project at
#        https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
#
# NOTE: For normal text-based Laxree challans, NONE of the above is needed.
# The text+regex extraction handles everything with no API key.


